  <Subject Subject_ID="300007805">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300007800</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>road transportation structures [300007800], transportation buildings [300007736], transportation structures [300120693], single built works by function [300004894], single built works by specific type [300004795], single built works (built environment) [300004790], Single Built Works (hierarchy name) [300004789], Built Environment (hierarchy name) [300264550], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Use only for intermediate stops along bus routes, usually containing sales and service facilities; use "bus shelters" for structures at bus stops affording weather protection but having no sales or service facilities; use "bus terminals" only to refer to buildings or other structures located at bus route endpoints.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese únicamente para designar una parada intermedia a lo largo de las rutas de los autobuses, generalmente conteniendo instalaciones de venta y servicios. Use "paradero de autobuses” para estructuras situadas en las paradas de los autobuses que proporcionan protección frente al tiempo, pero que no tienen instalaciones de ventas o servicios. Usar "terminal de autobuses” únicamente en referencia a los edificios u otro tipo de estructuras localizadas en los puntos finales de las rutas</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt alleen gebruikt voor tussenliggende haltes langs busroutes, meestal met verkoop- en servicevoorzieningen; gebruik 'wachthokjes' voor bouwwerken bij bushaltes die bescherming tegen het weer bieden maar geen verkoop- en servicevoorzieningen. Gebruik 'eindhaltes' alleen voor gebouwen of andere constructies die zich bevinden aan de eindpunten van busroutes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wird nur für Zwischenstationen entlang einer Buslinie verwendet, meist Verkaufs- und Serviceeinrichtungen beinhaltend; für ein Gebäude an Bushaltestellen, das Schutz vor der Witterung bietet, aber keine Verkaufs- oder Serviceeinrichtungen besitzt, ist "Wartehäuschen" zu verwenden; für ein Gebäude oder ein anderes Bauwerk, das sich an den Endpunkten einer Buslinie befindet, ist "zentraler Omnibusbahnhof" zu verwenden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>只用來表示公車路線途中的停車站，通常備有銷售和服務設施。「公車候車亭」一詞則表示位在各公車停靠站的結構物，提供遮風蔽雨保護，但無銷售或服務設施。「公車終站」一詞則只用來指公車路線終點的建築物或其他結構物。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Use apenas para paradas intermediárias ao longo de rotas de ônibus, geralmente contendo pontos de venda e serviços; usar "abrigos de ônibus" para estruturas em pontos de ônibus que ofereçam proteção contra intempéries, mas não tenham vendas ou instalações de serviço; use "terminais de ônibus" apenas para se referir a edifícios ou outras estruturas localizadas em pontos finais de rotas de ônibus.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
